" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2531946\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 26, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104sfb1665702556960.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/sfb1665702556960.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/sfb1665702556960.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"sfb1665702556960\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Default Packing Codes and Display Formats per Data Type\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"sfb1665702556960__default_packing_codes_and_display_formats_per_data_type_136656\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">If no packing code or field interface code is defined in the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Database Interface</span> for a field, Uniface uses a default packing code based on the data type. Some packing codes are also associated with a default display format.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"sfb1665702556960__p_d44399e1_d44400e1_d44401e1\">The default packing code and associated layout may not be the most appropriate, so we recommend that you specify a packing code in the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Database Interface</span>, and if necessary, a display format in the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Field Layout</span> property.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"sfb1665702556960__p_d44402e1_d44403e1_d44404e1\">The table shows the default packing codes that Uniface presents to the DBMS connectors when no packing code is specified. This does not mean that the defaults are passed on unchanged by the DBMS connectors. The DBMS connector determines the optimum storage format for that combination of data type and packing code.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"4\" id=\"sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Default Packing Code and Display Format per Data Type</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1__entry__1\">\n Uniface Data Type\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1__entry__2\">\n Data Type Code\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1__entry__3\">\n Default Packing Code\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1__entry__4\">\n Default Display Format\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1__entry__1\">\n Boolean\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1__entry__2\">\n B\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1__entry__3\">\n B\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1__entry__4\">\n DIS(T|F)\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1__entry__1\">\n Date\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1__entry__2\">\n D\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1__entry__3\">\n D\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1__entry__4\">\n DIS(ddmmyyyy)\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1__entry__1\">\n Datetime\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1__entry__2\">\n E\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1__entry__3\">\n E\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1__entry__4\">\n DIS(dd-MMM-yyyy hhnnss)\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1__entry__1\">\n Float\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1__entry__2\">\n F\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1__entry__3\">\n F\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1__entry__4\">\n —\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1__entry__1\">Image <sup class=\"ph sup\">1</sup>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1__entry__2\">\n I\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1__entry__3\">\n R\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1__entry__4\">\n —\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1__entry__1\">\n Linear Date\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1__entry__2\">\n LD\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1__entry__3\">\n D\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1__entry__4\">\n DIS(ddmmyyyy)\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1__entry__1\">\n Linear Datetime\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1__entry__2\">\n LE\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1__entry__3\">\n E\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1__entry__4\">\n DIS(dd-MMM-yyyy hhnnss)\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1__entry__1\">\n Linear Time\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1__entry__2\">\n LT\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1__entry__3\">\n T\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1__entry__4\">\n DIS(hh:nn:ss)\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1__entry__1\">\n Numeric\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1__entry__2\">\n N\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1__entry__3\">\n F\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1__entry__4\">\n —\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1__entry__1\">Raw <sup class=\"ph sup\">2</sup>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1__entry__2\">\n R\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1__entry__3\">\n R\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1__entry__4\">\n —\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1__entry__1\">\n String\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1__entry__2\">\n S\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1__entry__3\">\n C40\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1__entry__4\">\n —\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1__entry__1\">\n Time\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1__entry__2\">\n T\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1__entry__3\">\n T\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1__entry__4\">\n DIS(hh:nn:ss)\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1__entry__1\">\n XML stream\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1__entry__2\">\n XM\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1__entry__3\">\n VC*\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1__entry__4\">\n —\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" colspan=\"4\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1__entry__1 sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1__entry__2 sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1__entry__3 sfb1665702556960__table_d4268e1_d4269e1_d4270e1__entry__4\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n                        Notes: \n                     </p>\n<ol class=\"ol\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"sfb1665702556960__li_d22154e1_d22155e1_d22156e1\">The Image data type can be used only for images and glyphs.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"sfb1665702556960__li_d22157e1_d22158e1_d22159e1\">The Raw data type allows the full Uniface character set. The default character set for all other data types is CP1252 (on Microsoft Windows). This default can be changed by specifying an allowed character set in the syntax model (see <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$DEF_CHARSET</span>).\n </li>\n</ol>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wop1665702530947.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Storage Formats</a><p>DBMS vendors use the term data type to describe the way data is handled and stored on disk, but this invariably means the way the data is actually stored. In Uniface documentation, the term storage format is therefore used to refer to DBMS data types . A Uniface data type is specified for each field in a modeled entity; a DBMS storage format is internal to the DBMS.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cin1665702912680.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Format Conversions Between Uniface and DBMS Connector</a><p>To ensure that every Uniface packing code can be used with every supported DBMS, even if the underlying DBMS does not support that packing code, Uniface uses information from the individual database connectors. When first activated, a database connector presents to Uniface a full table of packing code mappings in which every packing code not supported by the DBMS is remapped to an alternative format.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ckh1665702551507.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Display Formats</a><p>Display formats control the way the data is displayed, as opposed to the way it is stored.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yyf1665702556802.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Database Interface (Fields)</a><p>This property (also known as the field interface) determines how data in the field is physically stored in the database.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lpv1665702557117.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Field Layout</a><p>Property that specifies how the field's data is formatted for display. The value can be a comma-separated list of shorthand codes, or a reference to a modeled field layout.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531946\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531946\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Default Packing Codes and Display Formats per Data Type Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 26, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Default Packing Codes and Display Formats per Data Type If no packing code or field interface code is defined in the Database Interface for a field, Uniface uses a default packing code based on the data type. Some packing codes are also associated with a default display format. The default packing code and associated layout may not be the most appropriate, so we recommend that you specify a packing code in the Database Interface , and if necessary, a display format in the Field Layout property. The table shows the default packing codes that Uniface presents to the DBMS connectors when no packing code is specified. This does not mean that the defaults are passed on unchanged by the DBMS connectors. The DBMS connector determines the optimum storage format for that combination of data type and packing code. Table 1. Default Packing Code and Display Format per Data Type Uniface Data Type Data Type Code Default Packing Code Default Display Format Boolean B B DIS(T|F) Date D D DIS(ddmmyyyy) Datetime E E DIS(dd-MMM-yyyy hhnnss) Float F F — Image 1 I R — Linear Date LD D DIS(ddmmyyyy) Linear Datetime LE E DIS(dd-MMM-yyyy hhnnss) Linear Time LT T DIS(hh:nn:ss) Numeric N F — Raw 2 R R — String S C40 — Time T T DIS(hh:nn:ss) XML stream XM VC* — Notes: The Image data type can be used only for images and glyphs. The Raw data type allows the full Uniface character set. The default character set for all other data types is CP1252 (on Microsoft Windows). This default can be changed by specifying an allowed character set in the syntax model (see $DEF_CHARSET ). Related Links Storage Formats DBMS vendors use the term data type to describe the way data is handled and stored on disk, but this invariably means the way the data is actually stored. In Uniface documentation, the term storage format is therefore used to refer to DBMS data types . A Uniface data type is specified for each field in a modeled entity; a DBMS storage format is internal to the DBMS. Format Conversions Between Uniface and DBMS Connector To ensure that every Uniface packing code can be used with every supported DBMS, even if the underlying DBMS does not support that packing code, Uniface uses information from the individual database connectors. When first activated, a database connector presents to Uniface a full table of packing code mappings in which every packing code not supported by the DBMS is remapped to an alternative format. Display Formats Display formats control the way the data is displayed, as opposed to the way it is stored. Database Interface (Fields) This property (also known as the field interface) determines how data in the field is physically stored in the database. Field Layout Property that specifies how the field's data is formatted for display. The value can be a comma-separated list of shorthand codes, or a reference to a modeled field layout. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}